node.text:
😂😂😂

THERE IS NO SUCH THING AS “FULL COVERAGE” INSURANCE!!

Here is what NEEDS to be on your insurance policy:

- Comprehensive and collision coverage (to protect your vehicle fully)

- Uninsured motorist coverage and medical payments coverage (to cover your injuries)

Remember: with uninsured motorist coverage you want the “add-on” type for both property damage and bodily injury.

This way, if you ever get in an accident you can rest assured that you’ll make #AwadOfMoney

Need legal help after an accident? Send me a message any time 📩

node.text:
After meeting with two different lawyers this week who each have firms making $80M-$90M annually, I’ve realized a few things. 

Millionaires aren’t usually geniuses. 

There is no minimum intelligence requirement to achieve wealth. 

You just have to do one thing consistently, and become the best at it so other people hire you instead of doing it on their own.

That’s literally it. 

Yes you will need to implement processes, hire teams, build infrastructure, etc., but the fundamentals remain the same:

Do one thing exceptionally well for a long period of time (assuming it’s a high income skill or has high income potential), and you will become a millionaire. 

Billionaires, on the other hand, are innovators. 

They’re visionaries. 

They hate the status quo and want to do everything better than everyone else. 

They find the best people in the world, and figure out how to beat them. 

Billionaires don’t want to just be the best, they want to revolutionize the way things are done. 

Always thinking about how to improve life and make things simpler for the consumer. 

Billionaires, in my opinion, are usually brilliant. 

Case in point: there are a ton of dumb self-made millionaires out there. 

But a self-made idiot billionaire? Impossible. 

Do you agree?
